fr:mainmatter.fr:p: Researcher with formal background in polymer chemistry, semiconductor fabrication & computer science. I received a PhD in Chemical Engineering (dissertation) from The University of Texas at Austin in 2017, as a student of Prof. C. Grant Willson.
My professional experience includes 5 1/2 years at OculusFacebook/Meta Reality Labs, where I developed new polymeric films & coatings for waveguide-based AR devices.
Currently, I am finishing my Masters in Computer Science at Georgia Tech (OMSCS) with a focus in Artificial Intelligence.
My publication record includes 96 publications, including patents and conference presentations.

Researcher with formal background in polymer chemistry, semiconductor fabrication & computer science. I received a PhD in Chemical Engineering (dissertation) from The University of Texas at Austin in 2017, as a student of Prof. C. Grant Willson.
My professional experience includes 5 1/2 years at OculusFacebook/Meta Reality Labs, where I developed new polymeric films & coatings for waveguide-based AR devices.
Currently, I am finishing my Masters in Computer Science at Georgia Tech (OMSCS) with a focus in Artificial Intelligence.
My publication record includes 96 publications, including patents and conference presentations.
